Key Match Events: The Houston Rockets came away with their second straight win last night against the San Antonio Spurs, 127-100.
Point guard Fred VanVleet shot 11-for-12 from the field and 1-for-2 from deep to end with 21 points, seven rebounds, and 10 assists.
VanVleet's defense was elite, preventing Chris Paul from doing any serious damage.
Alperen Sengun finished with 16 points, five rebounds, four assists, one steal, and two blocks in just 24 minutes.
